## Early game

The Void's Corrupted enemies carry a noticeably higher Control Module drop
chance than any main-planet foe, and **Hepit** (Capture, levels 10-15) is a
short, low-level way to farm them. Because it's an enemy drop, a Resource Drop
Booster and Nekros Desecrate both help; a couple of quick runs back-to-back
also keeps the pace up. **Teshub** (Exterminate) on the same tileset is a good
alternative if Hepit's matchmaking is slow.

## Mid & late game

The natural extension for a Steel Path squad is an endless Void Survival like
**Mot** — it keeps you killing Corrupted for the longest uninterrupted window
in one sitting. Since Control Modules drop from those enemies, a Resource Drop
Booster, the Steel Path passive and a loot frame (Nekros/Khora) all stack, and
longer runs compound the total.

